Project Report on Automated Banking Website Using Agile
1. Introduction

An Automated Banking Website allows users to perform banking operations like checking balance, transferring money, and viewing transaction history online. This project is created to reduce manual work in banks and provide fast service to customers.

2. Objective

To provide online banking services

To manage user accounts securely

To allow fund transfer and transaction tracking

To improve banking efficiency

3. Scope

This project includes:

User registration and login

Account dashboard

Balance enquiry

Fund transfer

Transaction history

Admin section (optional)

4. Agile Methodology

Agile helps in developing banking features one by one and testing each part properly.

Sprints

Sprint 1: Login + account dashboard
Sprint 2: Balance enquiry + profile update
Sprint 3: Fund transfer + transaction history
Sprint 4: Testing + security improvements

5. Tools & Technologies

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

Backend: Java / PHP / Python

Database: MySQL

Tools: Eclipse, MySQL Workbench

6. Conclusion

Automated banking website is very useful for customers as it saves time and reduces bank workload. Agile development made the project easy to manage and improve step-by-step.
